<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,510,1146]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,452,762,787]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="1">General distribution.</emphasis>
Indo-West Pacific: Widely distributed across the Indo-West Pacific; 
<collectingCountry box="[1231,1378,762,786]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, Red Sea (
<typeStatus box="[206,256,798,822]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
locality) through Indian Ocean to the Hawaiian Is.; also recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1147,798,822]" name="Tunisia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
in the Mediterranean Sea under 
<taxonomicName box="[225,399,835,859]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassimanus">
<emphasis box="[225,242,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[259,399,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">crassimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Banner, D. M. &amp; Banner, A. H." box="[464,737,834,858]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref45509" refString="Banner, D. M. &amp; Banner, A. H. (1981) Annotated checklist of the Alpheid shrimp of the Red Sea and Gulf of Aden. Zoologische Verhandelingen, 190, 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1981">Banner &amp; Banner 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chace, F. A. Jr" box="[752,892,834,858]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref46156" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr (1988) The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albatross Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 1910, Part 5: Family Alpheidae. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 466, 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Chace 1988</bibRefCitation>
). This species entered the Mediterranean as an Erythrean alien by way of the Suez Canal (
<bibRefCitation author="Galil, B. S." box="[631,756,870,894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="377 - 401" refId="ref47288" refString="Galil, B. S. (2011) The Alien Crustaceans in the Mediterranean Sea: An Historical Review. In: Galil, B. S., Clark, P. F. &amp; Carlton, J. T. (eds): In the Wrong Place-Alien Marine Crustaceans: Distribution, Biology and Impacts. Ivading Nature, Springer Series in Invasion Ecology 6, 377 - 401." type="journal article" year="2011">Galil 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,510,1146]" box="[199,1006,906,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,906,931]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Muddy intertidal, estuaries, mangroves, rocky/cobble intrtidal.
</paragraph>
